{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Talkin' 'Bout Your Generation'' episodes}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2011}} ''[[Talkin' 'Bout Your Generation]]'' is an Australian game show produced by [[Granada Productions]] which premiered on [[Network Ten]] on 5 May 2009. It is hosted by [[Shaun Micallef]].<ref>{{TV Tonight|title=Micallef moonlights on TEN|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2009/01/micallef-moonlights-on-ten.html|date=22 January 2009|accessdate=22 January 2009}}</ref>
Series 1 ran for a total of 18 episodes, with the original production order extended due to the success of the show.<ref>[http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2009/07/ten-renews-talkin-bout-your-generation.html TEN renews Talkin' 'Bout Your Generation]</ref> A second series of 26 episodes began airing from 7 February 2010. Series 2 went on a planned hiatus as of Episode 10 on 18 April 2010. It returned with new episodes from 1 August 2010 and concluded with a Christmas special on 23 November 2010. Talkin' 'Bout Your Generation returned to its original timeslot of 7:30&nbsp;pm Tuesday from 7 September 2010.<ref>{{cite web|first=Andrew |last=B |url=http://www.throng.com.au/talkin-bout-your-generation/ten-your-gen-movin-nights-new-simpsons-remain-and-lie-me-finale |title=Ten: Your Gen movin' nights, new Simpsons remain and Lie to Me Finale. &#124; Junior Masterchef &#124; Lie To Me &#124; Modern Family &#124; Rules of Engagement &#124; Talkin' 'bout Your Generation &#124; News |publisher=Throng |date=20 August 2010 |accessdate=30 January 2011}}</ref> A third series began on 8 February 2011.<ref name="Airdate">{{TV Tonight|title=Airdate: Oprah âReunion.â Returning: Generation, GNW, Bondi Rescue.|url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2011/01/airdate-oprah-reunion-returning-generation-gnw-bondi-rescue.html|date=25 January 2011|accessdate=30 January 2011}}</ref>
